{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3952,"text":"\"I felt a Funeral, in my Brain,"},{"time":7838,"text":"and Mourners to and fro"},{"time":10240,"text":"kept treading -- treading --\ntill [it seemed]"},{"time":13067,"text":"that Sense was breaking through --"},{"time":15836,"text":"And when they all were seated,"},{"time":17605,"text":"a Service, like a Drum --"},{"time":19603,"text":"kept beating -- beating --\ntill I [thought]"},{"time":23079,"text":"my Mind was going numb --"},{"time":25831,"text":"And then I heard them lift a Box\nand creak across my Soul"},{"time":29994,"text":"with those same Boots of Lead, again,"},{"time":33053,"text":"then Space -- began to toll,"},{"time":36070,"text":"As [all] the Heavens were a Bell,\nand Being, [but] an Ear,"},{"time":40201,"text":"and I, and Silence, some strange Race,"},{"time":43284,"text":"wrecked, solitary, here --"},{"time":46493,"text":"[And] then a Plank in Reason, broke,"},{"time":49670,"text":"and I fell down and down --"},{"time":53011,"text":"and hit a World, at every plunge,"},{"time":55686,"text":"and Finished knowing -- then --\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":60198,"text":"We know depression through metaphors."},{"time":63680,"text":"Emily Dickinson was able\nto convey it in language,"},{"time":67389,"text":"Goya in an image."},{"time":70238,"text":"Half the purpose of art\nis to describe such iconic states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75997,"text":"As for me, I had always\nthought myself tough,"},{"time":79875,"text":"one of the people who could survive"},{"time":81701,"text":"if I'd been sent to a concentration camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84614,"text":"In 1991, I had a series of losses."},{"time":87676,"text":"My mother died,"},{"time":89198,"text":"a relationship I'd been in ended,"},{"time":91324,"text":"I moved back to the United States\nfrom some years abroad,"},{"time":95268,"text":"and I got through all of those\nexperiences intact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98617,"text":"But in 1994, three years later,"},{"time":101540,"text":"I found myself losing interest\nin almost everything."},{"time":106059,"text":"I didn't want to do any of the things\nI had previously wanted to do,"},{"time":109959,"text":"and I didn't know why."},{"time":111987,"text":"The opposite of depression\nis not happiness, but vitality."},{"time":117127,"text":"And it was vitality"},{"time":118595,"text":"that seemed to seep away\nfrom me in that moment."},{"time":122231,"text":"Everything there was to do\nseemed like too much work."},{"time":126597,"text":"I would come home"},{"time":128058,"text":"and I would see the red light\nflashing on my answering machine,"},{"time":131410,"text":"and instead of being thrilled\nto hear from my friends,"},{"time":133974,"text":"I would think,"},{"time":135187,"text":"\"What a lot of people that is\nto have to call back.\""},{"time":138368,"text":"Or I would decide I should have lunch,"},{"time":140954,"text":"and then I would think,\nbut I'd have to get the food out"},{"time":143715,"text":"and put it on a plate"},{"time":145501,"text":"and cut it up and chew it and swallow it,"},{"time":149389,"text":"and it felt to me\nlike the Stations of the Cross."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153286,"text":"And one of the things that often gets lost\nin discussions of depression"},{"time":157443,"text":"is that you know it's ridiculous."},{"time":159801,"text":"You know it's ridiculous\nwhile you're experiencing it."},{"time":162768,"text":"You know that most people manage"},{"time":164681,"text":"to listen to their messages and eat lunch"},{"time":166995,"text":"and organize themselves to take a shower"},{"time":168925,"text":"and go out the front door"},{"time":170167,"text":"and that it's not a big deal,"},{"time":171819,"text":"and yet you are nonetheless in its grip"},{"time":174985,"text":"and you are unable to figure out\nany way around it."},{"time":178990,"text":"And so I began to feel myself doing less"},{"time":183236,"text":"and thinking less"},{"time":185546,"text":"and feeling less."},{"time":187829,"text":"It was a kind of nullity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190049,"text":"And then the anxiety set in."},{"time":192567,"text":"If you told me that I'd have to be\ndepressed for the next month,"},{"time":196283,"text":"I would say, \"As long I know it'll be over\nin November, I can do it.\""},{"time":199546,"text":"But if you said to me,"},{"time":200816,"text":"\"You have to have acute anxiety\nfor the next month,\""},{"time":204153,"text":"I would rather slit my wrist\nthan go through it."},{"time":206496,"text":"It was the feeling all the time"},{"time":208078,"text":"like that feeling you have\nif you're walking"},{"time":210306,"text":"and you slip or trip\nand the ground is rushing up at you,"},{"time":213851,"text":"but instead of lasting half a second,\nthe way that does,"},{"time":216587,"text":"it lasted for six months."},{"time":218492,"text":"It's a sensation\nof being afraid all the time"},{"time":221445,"text":"but not even knowing\nwhat it is that you're afraid of."},{"time":225057,"text":"And it was at that point\nthat I began to think"},{"time":227692,"text":"that it was just too painful to be alive,"},{"time":231476,"text":"and that the only reason\nnot to kill oneself"},{"time":234060,"text":"was so as not to hurt other people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237295,"text":"And finally one day, I woke up"},{"time":240200,"text":"and I thought perhaps I'd had a stroke,"},{"time":242421,"text":"because I lay in bed completely frozen,"},{"time":244939,"text":"looking at the telephone, thinking,"},{"time":246888,"text":"\"Something is wrong\nand I should call for help,\""},{"time":250451,"text":"and I couldn't reach out my arm"},{"time":252186,"text":"and pick up the phone and dial."},{"time":254801,"text":"And finally, after four full hours\nof my lying and staring at it,"},{"time":258876,"text":"the phone rang,"},{"time":260164,"text":"and somehow I managed to pick it up,"},{"time":262567,"text":"and it was my father, and I said,"},{"time":265519,"text":"\"I'm in serious trouble.\nWe need to do something.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":269528,"text":"The next day I started\nwith the medications and the therapy."},{"time":275352,"text":"And I also started reckoning\nwith this terrible question:"},{"time":279579,"text":"If I'm not the tough person"},{"time":281707,"text":"who could have made it\nthrough a concentration camp,"},{"time":284231,"text":"then who am I?"},{"time":285743,"text":"And if I have to take medication,"},{"time":287628,"text":"is that medication making me\nmore fully myself,"},{"time":291565,"text":"or is it making me someone else?"},{"time":293807,"text":"And how do I feel about it\nif it's making me someone else?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298101,"text":"I had two advantages\nas I went into the fight."},{"time":301585,"text":"The first is that I knew that,\nobjectively speaking,"},{"time":304280,"text":"I had a nice life,"},{"time":305901,"text":"and that if I could only get well,"},{"time":307786,"text":"there was something at the other end\nthat was worth living for."},{"time":311010,"text":"And the other was\nthat I had access to good treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314343,"text":"But I nonetheless emerged and relapsed,"},{"time":317816,"text":"and emerged and relapsed,"},{"time":320351,"text":"and emerged and relapsed,"},{"time":323369,"text":"and finally understood"},{"time":325333,"text":"I would have to be on medication\nand in therapy forever."},{"time":329769,"text":"And I thought,"},{"time":330960,"text":"\"But is it a chemical problem\nor a psychological problem?"},{"time":333770,"text":"And does it need a chemical cure\nor a philosophical cure?\""},{"time":337727,"text":"And I couldn't figure out which it was."},{"time":339878,"text":"And then I understood that actually,"},{"time":342002,"text":"we aren't advanced enough in either area\nfor it to explain things fully."},{"time":346013,"text":"The chemical cure\nand the psychological cure"},{"time":349364,"text":"both have a role to play,"},{"time":351062,"text":"and I also figured out\nthat depression was something"},{"time":355060,"text":"that was braided so deep into us"},{"time":357308,"text":"that there was no separating it\nfrom our character and personality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361552,"text":"I want to say that the treatments we have\nfor depression are appalling."},{"time":366038,"text":"They're not very effective."},{"time":367958,"text":"They're extremely costly."},{"time":369752,"text":"They come with innumerable side effects."},{"time":372273,"text":"They're a disaster."},{"time":374027,"text":"But I am so grateful that I live now\nand not 50 years ago,"},{"time":378718,"text":"when there would have been\nalmost nothing to be done."},{"time":381662,"text":"I hope that 50 years hence,"},{"time":384069,"text":"people will hear about my treatments"},{"time":386115,"text":"and be appalled that anyone endured\nsuch primitive science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390885,"text":"Depression is the flaw in love."},{"time":395441,"text":"If you were married\nto someone and thought,"},{"time":398582,"text":"\"Well, if my wife dies,\nI'll find another one,\""},{"time":402316,"text":"it wouldn't be love as we know it."},{"time":405364,"text":"There's no such thing as love\nwithout the anticipation of loss,"},{"time":409955,"text":"and that specter of despair\ncan be the engine of intimacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416204,"text":"There are three things\npeople tend to confuse:"},{"time":419059,"text":"depression, grief and sadness."},{"time":422966,"text":"Grief is explicitly reactive."},{"time":426329,"text":"If you have a loss\nand you feel incredibly unhappy,"},{"time":429234,"text":"and then, six months later,"},{"time":430933,"text":"you are still deeply sad,\nbut you're functioning a little better,"},{"time":434042,"text":"it's probably grief,"},{"time":435851,"text":"and it will probably ultimately\nresolve itself in some measure."},{"time":439610,"text":"If you experience a catastrophic loss,"},{"time":442439,"text":"and you feel terrible,"},{"time":443765,"text":"and six months later\nyou can barely function at all,"},{"time":446578,"text":"then it's probably a depression\nthat was triggered"},{"time":449116,"text":"by the catastrophic circumstances."},{"time":451648,"text":"The trajectory tells us a great deal."},{"time":455196,"text":"People think of depression\nas being just sadness."},{"time":458580,"text":"It's much, much too much sadness,"},{"time":460775,"text":"much too much grief"},{"time":462550,"text":"at far too slight a cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465470,"text":"As I set out to understand depression,"},{"time":468279,"text":"and to interview people\nwho had experienced it,"},{"time":470950,"text":"I found that there were people\nwho seemed, on the surface,"},{"time":474767,"text":"to have what sounded like\nrelatively mild depression"},{"time":478004,"text":"who were nonetheless\nutterly disabled by it."},{"time":481297,"text":"And there were other people\nwho had what sounded"},{"time":483734,"text":"as they described it\nlike terribly severe depression"},{"time":486820,"text":"who nonetheless had good lives"},{"time":488584,"text":"in the interstices\nbetween their depressive episodes."},{"time":491885,"text":"And I set out to find out\nwhat it is that causes some people"},{"time":495874,"text":"to be more resilient than other people."},{"time":498127,"text":"What are the mechanisms\nthat allow people to survive?"},{"time":501652,"text":"And I went out and I interviewed\nperson after person"},{"time":504874,"text":"who was suffering with depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506874,"text":"One of the first people I interviewed"},{"time":509089,"text":"described depression\nas a slower way of being dead,"},{"time":513967,"text":"and that was a good thing\nfor me to hear early on"},{"time":516325,"text":"because it reminded me\nthat that slow way of being dead"},{"time":519456,"text":"can lead to actual deadness,"},{"time":521760,"text":"that this is a serious business."},{"time":523741,"text":"It's the leading disability worldwide,"},{"time":526154,"text":"and people die of it every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529184,"text":"One of the people I talked to\nwhen I was trying to understand this"},{"time":532927,"text":"was a beloved friend\nwho I had known for many years,"},{"time":536812,"text":"and who had had a psychotic episode\nin her freshman year of college,"},{"time":541289,"text":"and then plummeted\ninto a horrific depression."},{"time":544115,"text":"She had bipolar illness,"},{"time":545778,"text":"or manic depression, as it was then known."},{"time":548289,"text":"And then she did very well\nfor many years on lithium,"},{"time":552098,"text":"and then eventually,\nshe was taken off her lithium"},{"time":555271,"text":"to see how she would do without it,"},{"time":557106,"text":"and she had another psychosis,"},{"time":559081,"text":"and then plunged into the worst depression\nthat I had ever seen"},{"time":563465,"text":"in which she sat\nin her parents' apartment,"},{"time":566306,"text":"more or less catatonic,\nessentially without moving,"},{"time":569602,"text":"day after day after day."},{"time":571943,"text":"And when I interviewed her\nabout that experience some years later --"},{"time":575451,"text":"she's a poet and psychotherapist\nnamed Maggie Robbins --"},{"time":578576,"text":"when I interviewed her, she said,"},{"time":581646,"text":"\"I was singing 'Where Have\nAll The Flowers Gone,'"},{"time":585189,"text":"over and over, to occupy my mind."},{"time":588555,"text":"I was singing to blot out\nthe things my mind was saying,"},{"time":591375,"text":"which were, 'You are nothing.\nYou are nobody."},{"time":596159,"text":"You don't even deserve to live.'"},{"time":598691,"text":"And that was\nwhen I really started thinking"},{"time":601121,"text":"about killing myself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":603193,"text":"You don't think in depression\nthat you've put on a gray veil"},{"time":607127,"text":"and are seeing the world\nthrough the haze of a bad mood."},{"time":611001,"text":"You think that the veil\nhas been taken away,"},{"time":614015,"text":"the veil of happiness,"},{"time":615643,"text":"and that now you're seeing truly."},{"time":618247,"text":"It's easier to help\nschizophrenics who perceive"},{"time":621031,"text":"that there's something foreign\ninside of them that needs to be exorcised,"},{"time":625029,"text":"but it's difficult with depressives,"},{"time":627379,"text":"because we believe\nwe are seeing the truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631040,"text":"But the truth lies."},{"time":633987,"text":"I became obsessed with that sentence:"},{"time":635985,"text":"\"But the truth lies.\""},{"time":638435,"text":"And I discovered,\nas I talked to depressive people,"},{"time":640899,"text":"that they have\nmany delusional perceptions."},{"time":643815,"text":"People will say, \"No one loves me.\""},{"time":645577,"text":"And you say, \"I love you,"},{"time":646813,"text":"your wife loves you,\nyour mother loves you.\""},{"time":649335,"text":"You can answer that one pretty readily,\nat least for most people."},{"time":653124,"text":"But people who are depressed\nwill also say,"},{"time":655314,"text":"\"No matter what we do,\nwe're all just going to die in the end.\""},{"time":659385,"text":"Or they'll say,\n\"There can be no true communion"},{"time":661638,"text":"between two human beings."},{"time":663024,"text":"Each of us is trapped in his own body.\""},{"time":665805,"text":"To which you have to say,"},{"time":667449,"text":"\"That's true,"},{"time":668952,"text":"but I think we should focus right now\non what to have for breakfast.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":672484,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674669,"text":"A lot of the time,"},{"time":676338,"text":"what they are expressing\nis not illness, but insight,"},{"time":679336,"text":"and one comes to think\nwhat's really extraordinary"},{"time":681891,"text":"is that most of us know\nabout those existential questions"},{"time":685047,"text":"and they don't distract us very much."},{"time":687428,"text":"There was a study I particularly liked"},{"time":689274,"text":"in which a group of depressed\nand a group of non-depressed people"},{"time":693041,"text":"were asked to play a video\ngame for an hour,"},{"time":695789,"text":"and at the end of the hour,"},{"time":697433,"text":"they were asked how many little monsters\nthey thought they had killed."},{"time":701067,"text":"The depressive group was usually accurate\nto within about 10 percent,"},{"time":705076,"text":"and the non-depressed people"},{"time":706671,"text":"guessed between 15 and 20 times\nas many little monsters --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":711149,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712324,"text":"as they had actually killed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715945,"text":"A lot of people said, when I chose\nto write about my depression,"},{"time":719185,"text":"that it must be very difficult\nto be out of that closet,"},{"time":722674,"text":"to have people know."},{"time":724007,"text":"They said, \"Do people\ntalk to you differently?\""},{"time":726300,"text":"I said, \"Yes, people\ntalk to me differently."},{"time":728403,"text":"They talk to me differently insofar"},{"time":730189,"text":"as they start telling me\nabout their experience,"},{"time":732880,"text":"or their sister's experience,"},{"time":734715,"text":"or their friend's experience."},{"time":736729,"text":"Things are different because now I know"},{"time":738951,"text":"that depression is the family secret\nthat everyone has."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743715,"text":"I went a few years ago to a conference,"},{"time":747365,"text":"and on Friday of the three-day conference,"},{"time":749820,"text":"one of the participants\ntook me aside, and she said,"},{"time":752849,"text":"\"I suffer from depression\nand I'm a little embarrassed about it,"},{"time":759122,"text":"but I've been taking this medication,"},{"time":760988,"text":"and I just wanted to ask you\nwhat you think?\""},{"time":764126,"text":"And so I did my best to give her\nsuch advice as I could."},{"time":766770,"text":"And then she said, \"You know,\nmy husband would never understand this."},{"time":771281,"text":"He's really the kind of guy to whom\nthis wouldn't make any sense,"},{"time":774573,"text":"so, you know, it's just between us.\""},{"time":776721,"text":"And I said, \"Yes, that's fine.\""},{"time":778733,"text":"On Sunday of the same conference,"},{"time":780616,"text":"her husband took me aside,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782516,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783854,"text":"and he said, \"My wife wouldn't think"},{"time":785639,"text":"that I was really much\nof a guy if she knew this,"},{"time":787974,"text":"but I've been dealing with this depression\nand I'm taking some medication,"},{"time":791756,"text":"and I wondered what you think?\""},{"time":794205,"text":"They were hiding the same medication"},{"time":796519,"text":"in two different places\nin the same bedroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799918,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":801140,"text":"And I said that I thought\ncommunication within the marriage"},{"time":804102,"text":"might be triggering\nsome of their problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810593,"text":"But I was also struck"},{"time":812180,"text":"by the burdensome nature\nof such mutual secrecy."},{"time":816141,"text":"Depression is so exhausting."},{"time":818026,"text":"It takes up so much\nof your time and energy,"},{"time":820996,"text":"and silence about it,"},{"time":822551,"text":"it really does make the depression worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825276,"text":"And then I began thinking"},{"time":826509,"text":"about all the ways\npeople make themselves better."},{"time":828856,"text":"I'd started off as a medical conservative."},{"time":831341,"text":"I thought there were a few\nkinds of therapy that worked,"},{"time":833999,"text":"it was clear what they were --"},{"time":835468,"text":"there was medication,"},{"time":836992,"text":"there were certain psychotherapies,"},{"time":838683,"text":"there was possibly\nelectroconvulsive treatment,"},{"time":841128,"text":"and that everything else was nonsense."},{"time":843741,"text":"But then I discovered something."},{"time":845693,"text":"If you have brain cancer,"},{"time":847350,"text":"and you say that standing on your head\nfor 20 minutes every morning"},{"time":850562,"text":"makes you feel better,"},{"time":851739,"text":"it may make you feel better,\nbut you still have brain cancer,"},{"time":854741,"text":"and you'll still probably die from it."},{"time":857387,"text":"But if you say that you have depression,"},{"time":859697,"text":"and standing on your head\nfor 20 minutes every day"},{"time":862061,"text":"makes you feel better, then it's worked,"},{"time":864281,"text":"because depression\nis an illness of how you feel,"},{"time":866746,"text":"and if you feel better,"},{"time":868100,"text":"then you are effectively\nnot depressed anymore."},{"time":871112,"text":"So I became much more tolerant"},{"time":873223,"text":"of the vast world\nof alternative treatments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875936,"text":"And I get letters,\nI get hundreds of letters"},{"time":878272,"text":"from people writing to tell me\nabout what's worked for them."},{"time":881106,"text":"Someone was asking me\nbackstage today about meditation."},{"time":884695,"text":"My favorite of the letters that I got\nwas the one that came from a woman"},{"time":888391,"text":"who wrote and said\nthat she had tried therapy, medication,"},{"time":891336,"text":"she had tried pretty much everything,"},{"time":893190,"text":"and she had found a solution\nand hoped I would tell the world,"},{"time":896120,"text":"and that was making\nlittle things from yarn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899716,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":902633,"text":"She sent me some of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904193,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":906247,"text":"And I'm not wearing them right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908136,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":909845,"text":"I suggested to her\nthat she also should look up"},{"time":912360,"text":"obsessive compulsive disorder in the DSM."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916979,"text":"And yet, when I went to look\nat alternative treatments,"},{"time":919693,"text":"I also gained perspective\non other treatments."},{"time":922605,"text":"I went through\na tribal exorcism in Senegal"},{"time":925347,"text":"that involved a great deal of ram's blood"},{"time":927360,"text":"and that I'm not going\nto detail right now,"},{"time":929422,"text":"but a few years afterwards\nI was in Rwanda,"},{"time":931446,"text":"working on a different project,"},{"time":933367,"text":"and I happened to describe\nmy experience to someone,"},{"time":935976,"text":"and he said,"},{"time":937159,"text":"\"Well, that's West Africa,\nand we're in East Africa,"},{"time":939641,"text":"and our rituals are\nin some ways very different,"},{"time":941922,"text":"but we do have some rituals"},{"time":943247,"text":"that have something in common\nwith what you're describing.\""},{"time":946071,"text":"And he said,"},{"time":947262,"text":"\"But we've had a lot of trouble\nwith Western mental health workers,"},{"time":950497,"text":"especially the ones who came\nright after the genocide.\""},{"time":953139,"text":"I said, \"What kind\nof trouble did you have?\""},{"time":955213,"text":"And he said, \"Well,\nthey would do this bizarre thing."},{"time":958989,"text":"They didn't take people out\nin the sunshine"},{"time":961061,"text":"where you begin to feel better."},{"time":962574,"text":"They didn't include drumming\nor music to get people's blood going."},{"time":965750,"text":"They didn't involve the whole community."},{"time":967680,"text":"They didn't externalize\nthe depression as an invasive spirit."},{"time":970940,"text":"Instead what they did was they took people\none at a time into dingy little rooms"},{"time":975977,"text":"and had them talk for an hour"},{"time":977382,"text":"about bad things\nthat had happened to them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":979550,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":981617,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":985010,"text":"He said, \"We had to ask them\nto leave the country.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":987463,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":990429,"text":"Now at the other end\nof alternative treatments,"},{"time":993031,"text":"let me tell you about Frank Russakoff."},{"time":995150,"text":"Frank Russakoff had the worst depression\nperhaps that I've ever seen in a man."},{"time":1000876,"text":"He was constantly depressed."},{"time":1002869,"text":"He was, when I met him,"},{"time":1004338,"text":"at a point at which every month,\nhe would have electroshock treatment."},{"time":1008168,"text":"Then he would feel\nsort of disoriented for a week."},{"time":1010743,"text":"Then he would feel okay for a week."},{"time":1012546,"text":"Then he would have a week\nof going downhill."},{"time":1014664,"text":"And then he would have another\nelectroshock treatment."},{"time":1017278,"text":"And he said to me when I met him,"},{"time":1018875,"text":"\"It's unbearable to go\nthrough my weeks this way."},{"time":1021264,"text":"I can't go on this way,"},{"time":1022735,"text":"and I've figured out\nhow I'm going to end it"},{"time":1024869,"text":"if I don't get better.\""},{"time":1026226,"text":"\"But,\" he said to me,\n\"I heard about a protocol at Mass General"},{"time":1030352,"text":"for a procedure called a cingulotomy,\nwhich is a brain surgery,"},{"time":1033598,"text":"and I think I'm going to give that a try.\""},{"time":1035891,"text":"And I remember being amazed\nat that point to think that someone"},{"time":1039208,"text":"who clearly had so many bad experiences"},{"time":1042229,"text":"with so many different treatments"},{"time":1044389,"text":"still had buried in him,\nsomewhere, enough optimism"},{"time":1047453,"text":"to reach out for one more."},{"time":1049760,"text":"And he had the cingulotomy,\nand it was incredibly successful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053981,"text":"He's now a friend of mine."},{"time":1055617,"text":"He has a lovely wife\nand two beautiful children."},{"time":1058966,"text":"He wrote me a letter\nthe Christmas after the surgery,"},{"time":1061915,"text":"and he said,"},{"time":1063104,"text":"\"My father sent me two presents this year,"},{"time":1065731,"text":"First, a motorized CD rack\nfrom The Sharper Image"},{"time":1068282,"text":"that I didn't really need,"},{"time":1069704,"text":"but I knew he was giving it\nto me to celebrate"},{"time":1071965,"text":"the fact that I'm living on my own\nand have a job I seem to love."},{"time":1075635,"text":"And the other present\nwas a photo of my grandmother,"},{"time":1078900,"text":"who committed suicide."},{"time":1080955,"text":"As I unwrapped it, I began to cry,"},{"time":1083884,"text":"and my mother came over and said,"},{"time":1085765,"text":"'Are you crying because\nof the relatives you never knew?'"},{"time":1089162,"text":"And I said, 'She had\nthe same disease I have.'"},{"time":1093242,"text":"I'm crying now as I write to you."},{"time":1095878,"text":"It's not that I'm so sad,\nbut I get overwhelmed,"},{"time":1099189,"text":"I think, because I could\nhave killed myself,"},{"time":1101410,"text":"but my parents kept me going,\nand so did the doctors,"},{"time":1104862,"text":"and I had the surgery."},{"time":1106716,"text":"I'm alive and grateful."},{"time":1109531,"text":"We live in the right time,\neven if it doesn't always feel like it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115856,"text":"I was struck by the fact that depression"},{"time":1117799,"text":"is broadly perceived to be\na modern, Western, middle-class thing,"},{"time":1122829,"text":"and I went to look at how it operated\nin a variety of other contexts,"},{"time":1126984,"text":"and one of the things\nI was most interested in"},{"time":1129199,"text":"was depression among the indigent."},{"time":1131138,"text":"And so I went out to try to look"},{"time":1132710,"text":"at what was being done\nfor poor people with depression."},{"time":1135487,"text":"And what I discovered is that poor people"},{"time":1137638,"text":"are mostly not being\ntreated for depression."},{"time":1140190,"text":"Depression is the result\nof a genetic vulnerability,"},{"time":1142888,"text":"which is presumably\nevenly distributed in the population,"},{"time":1146262,"text":"and triggering circumstances,"},{"time":1147999,"text":"which are likely to be more severe\nfor people who are impoverished."},{"time":1151777,"text":"And yet it turns out that if you have\na really lovely life"},{"time":1155304,"text":"but feel miserable all the time,"},{"time":1156910,"text":"you think, \"Why do I feel like this?"},{"time":1158720,"text":"I must have depression.\""},{"time":1160013,"text":"And you set out to find treatment for it."},{"time":1162173,"text":"But if you have a perfectly awful life,"},{"time":1164129,"text":"and you feel miserable all the time,"},{"time":1165896,"text":"the way you feel\nis commensurate with your life,"},{"time":1168930,"text":"and it doesn't occur to you to think,"},{"time":1170809,"text":"\"Maybe this is treatable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172370,"text":"And so we have an epidemic in this country"},{"time":1175596,"text":"of depression among impoverished people"},{"time":1178278,"text":"that's not being picked up\nand that's not being treated"},{"time":1180874,"text":"and that's not being addressed,"},{"time":1182846,"text":"and it's a tragedy of a grand order."},{"time":1185219,"text":"And so I found an academic"},{"time":1186843,"text":"who was doing a research project\nin slums outside of D.C.,"},{"time":1190092,"text":"where she picked up women\nwho had come in for other health problems"},{"time":1193259,"text":"and diagnosed them with depression,"},{"time":1195038,"text":"and then provided six months\nof the experimental protocol."},{"time":1198134,"text":"One of them, Lolly, came in,"},{"time":1200463,"text":"and this is what she said\nthe day she came in."},{"time":1203069,"text":"She said, and she was a woman,\nby the way, who had seven children."},{"time":1207658,"text":"She said, \"I used to have a job\nbut I had to give it up"},{"time":1210467,"text":"because I couldn't go out of the house."},{"time":1213134,"text":"I have nothing to say to my children."},{"time":1215447,"text":"In the morning,\nI can't wait for them to leave,"},{"time":1217953,"text":"and then I climb in bed\nand pull the covers over my head,"},{"time":1221179,"text":"and three o'clock when they come home,"},{"time":1223078,"text":"it just comes so fast.\""},{"time":1224544,"text":"She said, \"I've been taking\na lot of Tylenol,"},{"time":1226862,"text":"anything I can take\nso that I can sleep more."},{"time":1229389,"text":"My husband has been telling me\nI'm stupid, I'm ugly."},{"time":1233410,"text":"I wish I could stop the pain.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1236935,"text":"Well, she was brought\ninto this experimental protocol,"},{"time":1239555,"text":"and when I interviewed her\nsix months later,"},{"time":1241770,"text":"she had taken a job working in childcare"},{"time":1246019,"text":"for the U.S. Navy,\nshe had left the abusive husband,"},{"time":1250093,"text":"and she said to me,"},{"time":1252140,"text":"\"My kids are so much happier now.\""},{"time":1254419,"text":"She said, \"There's one room\nin my new place for the boys"},{"time":1257125,"text":"and one room for the girls,"},{"time":1259036,"text":"but at night, they're just\nall up on my bed,"},{"time":1261399,"text":"and we're doing homework\nall together and everything."},{"time":1264011,"text":"One of them wants to be a preacher,"},{"time":1265709,"text":"one of them wants to be a firefighter,"},{"time":1267626,"text":"and one of the girls says\nshe's going to be a lawyer."},{"time":1270350,"text":"They don't cry like they used to,"},{"time":1272578,"text":"and they don't fight like they did."},{"time":1275144,"text":"That's all I need now, is my kids."},{"time":1278826,"text":"Things keep on changing,"},{"time":1280795,"text":"the way I dress,\nthe way I feel, the way I act."},{"time":1285909,"text":"I can go outside not being afraid anymore,"},{"time":1289734,"text":"and I don't think\nthose bad feelings are coming back,"},{"time":1293246,"text":"and if it weren't\nfor Dr. Miranda and that,"},{"time":1296206,"text":"I would still be at home\nwith the covers pulled over my head,"},{"time":1299752,"text":"if I were still alive at all."},{"time":1302097,"text":"I asked the Lord to send me an angel,"},{"time":1305627,"text":"and He heard my prayers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1310308,"text":"I was really moved by these experiences,"},{"time":1313312,"text":"and I decided that I wanted\nto write about them"},{"time":1315851,"text":"not only in a book I was working on,\nbut also in an article,"},{"time":1318692,"text":"and I got a commission\nfrom The New York Times Magazine"},{"time":1321295,"text":"to write about depression\namong the indigent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1323438,"text":"And I turned in my story,"},{"time":1324699,"text":"and my editor called me and said,\n\"We really can't publish this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1328668,"text":"And I said, \"Why not?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1329851,"text":"And she said, \"It just is too far-fetched."},{"time":1331946,"text":"These people who are sort of\nat the very bottom rung of society"},{"time":1335633,"text":"and then they get\na few months of treatment"},{"time":1337672,"text":"and they're virtually ready\nto run Morgan Stanley?"},{"time":1340069,"text":"It's just too implausible.\""},{"time":1342013,"text":"She said, \"I've never even heard\nof anything like it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1344618,"text":"And I said, \"The fact\nthat you've never heard of it"},{"time":1347095,"text":"is an indication that it is news.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1349907,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1353954,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1357317,"text":"\"And you are a news magazine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1359950,"text":"So after a certain amount of negotiation,\nthey agreed to it."},{"time":1363034,"text":"But I think a lot of what they said\nwas connected in some strange way"},{"time":1366944,"text":"to this distaste that people still have\nfor the idea of treatment,"},{"time":1370549,"text":"the notion that somehow if we went out"},{"time":1372431,"text":"and treated a lot of people\nin indigent communities,"},{"time":1375278,"text":"that would be exploitative,"},{"time":1377158,"text":"because we would be changing them."},{"time":1378880,"text":"There is this false moral imperative\nthat seems to be all around us,"},{"time":1382711,"text":"that treatment of depression,"},{"time":1384843,"text":"the medications and so on,\nare an artifice,"},{"time":1387142,"text":"and that it's not natural."},{"time":1389489,"text":"And I think that's very misguided."},{"time":1392456,"text":"It would be natural\nfor people's teeth to fall out,"},{"time":1395813,"text":"but there is nobody militating\nagainst toothpaste,"},{"time":1399025,"text":"at least not in my circles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1401915,"text":"People then say,"},{"time":1403183,"text":"\"But isn't depression part of what people\nare supposed to experience?"},{"time":1406468,"text":"Didn't we evolve to have depression?"},{"time":1408224,"text":"Isn't it part of your personality?\""},{"time":1409999,"text":"To which I would say, mood is adaptive."},{"time":1412462,"text":"Being able to have sadness and fear"},{"time":1415563,"text":"and joy and pleasure"},{"time":1417493,"text":"and all of the other moods that we have,\nthat's incredibly valuable."},{"time":1421272,"text":"And major depression"},{"time":1423210,"text":"is something that happens\nwhen that system gets broken."},{"time":1426596,"text":"It's maladaptive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1428224,"text":"People will come to me and say,"},{"time":1429863,"text":"\"I think, though, if I just\nstick it out for another year,"},{"time":1432689,"text":"I think I can just get through this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1434566,"text":"And I always say to them,\n\"You may get through it,"},{"time":1437114,"text":"but you'll never be 37 again."},{"time":1439733,"text":"Life is short, and that's a whole year\nyou're talking about giving up."},{"time":1443982,"text":"Think it through.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1445694,"text":"It's a strange poverty\nof the English language,"},{"time":1448366,"text":"and indeed of many other languages,"},{"time":1450474,"text":"that we use this same word, depression,"},{"time":1452868,"text":"to describe how a kid feels\nwhen it rains on his birthday,"},{"time":1456606,"text":"and to describe how somebody feels\nthe minute before they commit suicide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1461495,"text":"People say to me, \"Well, is it\ncontinuous with normal sadness?\""},{"time":1464525,"text":"And I say, in a way it's continuous\nwith normal sadness."},{"time":1467656,"text":"There is a certain amount of continuity,"},{"time":1469854,"text":"but it's the same way there's continuity"},{"time":1471815,"text":"between having an iron fence\noutside your house"},{"time":1474045,"text":"that gets a little rust spot"},{"time":1475489,"text":"that you have to sand off\nand do a little repainting,"},{"time":1478111,"text":"and what happens if you leave\nthe house for 100 years"},{"time":1480963,"text":"and it rusts through\nuntil it's only a pile of orange dust."},{"time":1485082,"text":"And it's that orange dust spot,"},{"time":1486959,"text":"that orange dust problem,"},{"time":1488748,"text":"that's the one\nwe're setting out to address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1492040,"text":"So now people say,"},{"time":1494278,"text":"\"You take these happy pills,\nand do you feel happy?\""},{"time":1496981,"text":"And I don't."},{"time":1498594,"text":"But I don't feel sad\nabout having to eat lunch,"},{"time":1501586,"text":"and I don't feel sad\nabout my answering machine,"},{"time":1504451,"text":"and I don't feel sad\nabout taking a shower."},{"time":1507324,"text":"I feel more, in fact, I think,"},{"time":1509951,"text":"because I can feel\nsadness without nullity."},{"time":1512704,"text":"I feel sad about professional\ndisappointments,"},{"time":1516934,"text":"about damaged relationships,"},{"time":1519242,"text":"about global warming."},{"time":1521114,"text":"Those are the things\nthat I feel sad about now."},{"time":1523839,"text":"And I said to myself, well,\nwhat is the conclusion?"},{"time":1526573,"text":"How did those people who have better lives"},{"time":1529134,"text":"even with bigger depression\nmanage to get through?"},{"time":1531964,"text":"What is the mechanism of resilience?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1534583,"text":"And what I came up with over time"},{"time":1536569,"text":"was that the people\nwho deny their experience,"},{"time":1539419,"text":"and say, \"I was depressed a long time ago,"},{"time":1541459,"text":"I never want to think about it again,"},{"time":1543254,"text":"I'm not going to look at it"},{"time":1544572,"text":"and I'm just going\nto get on with my life,\""},{"time":1546619,"text":"ironically, those are the people\nwho are most enslaved by what they have."},{"time":1551241,"text":"Shutting out the depression\nstrengthens it."},{"time":1553780,"text":"While you hide from it, it grows."},{"time":1557185,"text":"And the people who do better"},{"time":1559747,"text":"are the ones who are able to tolerate\nthe fact that they have this condition."},{"time":1564324,"text":"Those who can tolerate their depression\nare the ones who achieve resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1568516,"text":"So Frank Russakoff said to me,"},{"time":1570152,"text":"\"If I had a do-over,\nI suppose I wouldn't do it this way,"},{"time":1573898,"text":"but in a strange way,\nI'm grateful for what I've experienced."},{"time":1577390,"text":"I'm glad to have been\nin the hospital 40 times."},{"time":1581023,"text":"It taught me so much about love,"},{"time":1583658,"text":"and my relationship\nwith my parents and my doctors"},{"time":1586603,"text":"has been so precious to me,\nand will be always.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1590772,"text":"And Maggie Robbins said,"},{"time":1592698,"text":"\"I used to volunteer in an AIDS clinic,"},{"time":1595687,"text":"and I would just talk and talk and talk,"},{"time":1598701,"text":"and the people I was dealing with\nweren't very responsive, and I thought,"},{"time":1602758,"text":"'That's not very friendly\nor helpful of them.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1605278,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1606542,"text":"\"And then I realized,"},{"time":1608184,"text":"I realized that\nthey weren't going to do more"},{"time":1610351,"text":"than make those first\nfew minutes of small talk."},{"time":1612858,"text":"It was simply going to be an occasion"},{"time":1614921,"text":"where I didn't have AIDS\nand I wasn't dying,"},{"time":1617894,"text":"but could tolerate the fact that they did"},{"time":1620796,"text":"and they were."},{"time":1622503,"text":"Our needs are our greatest assets."},{"time":1626202,"text":"It turns out I've learned to give\nall the things I need.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1632160,"text":"Valuing one's depression\ndoes not prevent a relapse,"},{"time":1636045,"text":"but it may make the prospect of relapse"},{"time":1638706,"text":"and even relapse itself\neasier to tolerate."},{"time":1643004,"text":"The question is not so much\nof finding great meaning"},{"time":1646686,"text":"and deciding your depression\nhas been very meaningful."},{"time":1649281,"text":"It's of seeking that meaning\nand thinking, when it comes again,"},{"time":1653296,"text":"\"This will be hellish,\nbut I will learn something from it.\""},{"time":1657487,"text":"I have learned in my own depression"},{"time":1659751,"text":"how big an emotion can be,"},{"time":1661973,"text":"how it can be more real than facts,"},{"time":1665057,"text":"and I have found that that experience"},{"time":1667810,"text":"has allowed me to experience\npositive emotion"},{"time":1670702,"text":"in a more intense and more focused way."},{"time":1674222,"text":"The opposite of depression\nis not happiness,"},{"time":1677829,"text":"but vitality,"},{"time":1679163,"text":"and these days, my life is vital,"},{"time":1682142,"text":"even on the days when I'm sad."},{"time":1684823,"text":"I felt that funeral in my brain,"},{"time":1687962,"text":"and I sat next to the colossus\nat the edge of the world,"},{"time":1692526,"text":"and I have discovered\nsomething inside of myself"},{"time":1696437,"text":"that I would have to call a soul"},{"time":1698525,"text":"that I had never formulated\nuntil that day 20 years ago"},{"time":1702062,"text":"when hell came to pay me a surprise visit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1706841,"text":"I think that while I hated being depressed"},{"time":1710678,"text":"and would hate to be depressed again,"},{"time":1713204,"text":"I've found a way to love my depression."},{"time":1715894,"text":"I love it because it has forced me\nto find and cling to joy."},{"time":1720681,"text":"I love it because each day I decide,"},{"time":1724294,"text":"sometimes gamely,"},{"time":1725707,"text":"and sometimes against the moment's reason,"},{"time":1728276,"text":"to cleave to the reasons for living."},{"time":1730978,"text":"And that, I think,\nis a highly privileged rapture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1735076,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1736356,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1740381,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1741556,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}